            "name": "ResizeSensor",
            "description": "Wrap a single element child and call `onResize` when it changes size. The child must be an element (a `ResizeObserver` needs a real DOM node to watch). ```tsx <ResizeSensor onResize={(entries) => setWidth(entries[0].contentRect.width)}> <div className=\"panel\" /> </ResizeSensor> ```",
